  "local_port": 50270,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which is the best camera phone performance under 10000?",
  "response": "Choosing the best camera phone under \u20b910,000 (assuming Indian Rupees) involves balancing camera quality with overall performance, battery life, and other features. As of 2023, several smartphones offer impressive camera capabilities within this budget. Here are some of the top contenders:\n\n### 1. **Redmi Note 11**\n- **Camera Setup:**\n  - **Rear:** 50 MP primary sensor, 8 MP ultra-wide, 2 MP macro, 2 MP depth sensor\n  - **Front:** 13 MP\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Display:** 6.43-inch FHD+ AMOLED, 90Hz refresh rate\n  - **Processor:** Qualcomm Snapdragon 680\n  - **Battery:** 5000 mAh with 33W fast charging\n- **Why It's Good:** The 50 MP primary camera delivers sharp and vibrant photos, and the AMOLED display enhances the viewing experience for media and photography.\n\n### 2. **Realme Narzo 50**\n- **Camera Setup:**\n  - **Rear:** 50 MP primary, 2 MP macro, 2 MP depth sensor\n  - **Front:** 8 MP\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Display:** 6.6-inch FHD+ IPS LCD, 90Hz refresh rate\n  - **Processor:** MediaTek Helio G96\n  - **Battery:** 5000 mAh with 33W Dart Charge\n- **Why It's Good:** Offers a high-resolution primary camera with decent performance in various lighting conditions. The fast charging and smooth display make it a balanced choice.\n\n### 3. **Samsung Galaxy F13**\n- **Camera Setup:**\n  - **Rear:** 50 MP primary, 5 MP ultra-wide, 2 MP macro\n  - **Front:** 8 MP\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Display:** 6.6-inch FHD+ TFT, 120Hz refresh rate\n  - **Processor:** Exynos 850\n  - **Battery:** 6000 mAh\n- **Why It's Good:** Known for reliable camera performance and Samsung's image processing. The large battery ensures extended usage without frequent recharging.\n\n### 4. **POCO M4 Pro**\n- **Camera Setup:**\n  - **Rear:** 64 MP primary, 2 MP macro, 2 MP depth sensor\n  - **Front:** 8 MP\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Display:** 6.6-inch FHD+ AMOLED, 90Hz refresh rate\n  - **Processor:** MediaTek Dimensity 810\n  - **Battery:** 5000 mAh with 33W fast charging\n- **Why It's Good:** The 64 MP main camera offers excellent detail and clarity. Coupled with a capable processor, it provides smooth performance alongside impressive photography.\n\n### 5. **Motorola Moto G31**\n- **Camera Setup:**\n  - **Rear:** 50 MP primary, 8 MP ultra-wide, 2 MP macro\n  - **Front:** 13 MP\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Display:** 6.4-inch OLED, 90Hz refresh rate\n  - **Processor:** MediaTek Helio G85\n  - **Battery:** 5000 mAh\n- **Why It's Good:** Offers a clean Android experience with reliable camera performance, especially in good lighting conditions. The OLED display provides vibrant colors and deep blacks.\n\n---\n\n### **Key Considerations When Choosing a Camera Phone Under \u20b910,000:**\n\n1. **Camera Specifications:**\n   - **Megapixels (MP):** Higher MP can mean more detail, but sensor quality and image processing are equally important.\n   - **Additional Lenses:** Ultra-wide, macro, and depth sensors add versatility to your photography.\n\n2. **Image Processing:**\n   - Software plays a crucial role in how photos turn out. Brands like Xiaomi and Samsung are known for their efficient image processing algorithms.\n\n3. **Low-Light Performance:**\n   - Phones with larger sensors and better software optimization perform better in low-light conditions.\n\n4. **Overall Performance:**\n   - Ensure the phone has a capable processor and sufficient RAM to handle everyday tasks smoothly alongside camera operations.\n\n5. **Battery Life:**\n   - A good camera phone should also offer long battery life, especially if you're frequently using the camera.\n\n6. **Display Quality:**\n   - An AMOLED or high-refresh-rate display can enhance your photography experience by displaying colors more accurately and smoothly.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nWhile several phones under \u20b910,000 offer commendable camera performance, the **Redmi Note 11** and **POCO M4 Pro** stand out due to their high-resolution primary cameras and balanced overall features. However, the best choice ultimately depends on your specific needs, such as preferred camera features, brand preference, and other usage requirements.\n\nBefore making a purchase, it's advisable to check the latest user reviews and possibly view sample photos online to ensure the phone meets your photography expectations.",
